+Material
  
  
  <section id="journalistic-translation" className="space-y-8">
          <h2 className="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Rules of Journalistic Translation
          </h2>

          {/* Introduction */}
          <div className="bg-white rounded-md shadow-md p-6">
            <p className="text-lg text-gray-700">
              Journalistic translation involves adapting headlines and articles
              while maintaining their **brevity, clarity, and cultural
              relevance**. The challenge is to **retain meaning** without
              compromising readability. This guide outlines **key differences**,
              **common pitfalls**, and **best practices** when translating
              between English and Arabic.
            </p>
          </div>

          {/* Translation Structure */}
          <div className="overflow-x-auto bg-white rounded-md shadow-md p-6">
            <table className="w-full table-auto">
              <tbody>
                {/* Inverted Pyramid Structure */}
                <tr className="bg-gray-200">
                  <th
                    colSpan={2}
                    className="px-4 py-2 text-gray-700 font-semibold"
                  >
                    Inverted Pyramid Structure in Headlines
                  </th>
                </tr>
                <tr className="border-b">
                  <td colSpan={2} className="px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">
                    <ul className="list-disc ml-4 text-lg">
                      <li>
                        Main Headline (Hard-News Lead) - Brief and direct.
                      </li>
                      <li>Supporting Sentences - Provide core news context.</li>
                      <li>
                        Details (Soft Leads) - Explanation and background
                        information.
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p className="mt-2 text-gray-700">
                      🔹 <span className="font-medium">Example:</span>
                      "Earthquake Hits California, Thousands Affected" follows
                      this structure.
                    </p>
                  </td>
                </tr>

                {/* English vs Arabic Headline Styles */}
                <tr className="bg-gray-200">
                  <th
                    colSpan={2}
                    className="px-4 py-2 text-gray-700 font-semibold"
                  >
                    Comparison: English vs. Arabic Headlines
                  </th>
                </tr>
                <tr className="border-b">
                  <td colSpan={2} className="px-4 py-2">
                    <div className="space-y-2">
                      <h4 className="text-lg font-semibold">
                        English Headlines
                      </h4>
                      <ul className="list-disc ml-4 text-lg">
                        <li>
                          Use telegraphic language (compressed, omitting "to
                          be").
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          Verbs often in present simple tense for past events.
                        </li>
                        <li>Definite articles are often dropped.</li>
                      </ul>
                      <p className="mt-2 text-gray-700">
                        🔹 <span className="font-medium">Example:</span>
                        "Egyptian President Meets US Officials" (instead of "The
                        Egyptian President is Meeting US Officials").
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div className="space-y-2 mt-2">
                      <h4 className="text-lg font-semibold">
                        Arabic Headlines
                      </h4>
                      <ul className="list-disc ml-4 text-lg">
                        <li>Mostly nominal sentences (without verbs).</li>
                        <li>Present tense used for future references.</li>
                        <li>
                          Verbs may be omitted completely in certain cases.
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                      <p className="mt-2 text-gray-700">
                        🔹 <span className="font-medium">Example:</span>
                        "زيارة رسمية للرئيس المصري إلى أمريكا" (A formal visit
                        by the Egyptian president to the U.S.).
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </td>
                </tr>

                {/* Examples of Translation */}
                <tr className="bg-gray-200">
                  <th
                    colSpan={2}
                    className="px-4 py-2 text-gray-700 font-semibold"
                  >
                    Examples: Translating Headlines
                  </th>
                </tr>
                <tr className="border-b">
                  <td colSpan={2} className="px-4 py-2">
                    <div className="space-y-2">
                      <h4 className="text-lg font-semibold">
                        English → Arabic
                      </h4>
                      <ul className="list-disc ml-4 text-lg">
                        <li>
                          <span className="font-medium">Original:</span>{" "}
                          Prosecutor orders release of 40 Cairo University
                          students detained for 8 months. <br />
                          <span className="font-medium">Translation:</span>{" "}
                          النيابة تفرج عن ٤٠ طالبًا من جامعة القاهرة بعد اعتقال
                          دام ثمانية أشهر
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <span className="font-medium">Original:</span> Obama
                          to visit Egypt <br />
                          <span className="font-medium">Translation:</span>{" "}
                          أوباما يزور مصر في مايو
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div className="space-y-2 mt-2">
                      <h4 className="text-lg font-semibold">
                        Arabic → English
                      </h4>
                      <ul className="list-disc ml-4 text-lg">
                        <li>
                          <span className="font-medium">Original:</span> اليوم
                          الرئيس يلقي خطابًا هامًا <br />
                          <span className="font-medium">Translation:</span>{" "}
                          President to deliver important speech today
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <span className="font-medium">Original:</span> مصر
                          تندد بالعدوان الإسرائيلي على غزة <br />
                          <span className="font-medium">Translation:</span>{" "}
                          Egypt condemns Israeli aggression on Gaza
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </td>
                </tr>

                {/* Common Challenges */}
                <tr className="bg-gray-200">
                  <th
                    colSpan={2}
                    className="px-4 py-2 text-gray-700 font-semibold"
                  >
                    Common Challenges in Journalistic Translation
                  </th>
                </tr>
                <tr className="border-b">
                  <td colSpan={2} className="px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">
                    <ul className="list-disc ml-4 text-lg">
                      <li>
                        Handling grammatical differences between English and
                        Arabic.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Ensuring brevity and clarity in Arabic while keeping the
                        original meaning.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Translating names of institutions, newspapers, and
                        idioms correctly.
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p className="mt-2 text-gray-700">
                      🔹 <span className="font-medium">Example:</span>
                      Instead of translating "Isratine" literally, use إسراطين
                      (a coined term for a proposed Israeli-Palestinian state).
                    </p>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>
